The paper deals with clustering relational data obtained from a database, which falls under the category of database systems (cs.DB). The paper also introduces a new algorithm for clustering, which involves leveraging the underlying structures in relational data, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the runtime improvements of the algorithm, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and cryptography and security (cs.CR).
